710741f-a.title: Manhattan: 11th Avenue - 58th Street (West)
710741f-a.text:
Eleventh Avenue, east side, north from 9. 58th (right) to
59th Streets, showing a fenced area where gas holders formerly
stood. Beyond 59th Street this thoroughfare changes its name
to become Vest End Avenue, therefomm the Empire Storage Varehouse
is at the N.W. corner of that and W. 59th Street.
September 19, 1933.
Views 1 and 2
P. L. Sperr
NO REPRODUCTIONS.
The New York Sun of September 29, 1938 reports the demolition
of No. 2-10 West End Avenue and 557-63 Aest 59th Street, a five
story warehouse formerly occupied by the National Gum and Mica Co.
This appears in this view as the Empire Storage Warehouse Co.

710740f-a.title: Manhattan: 11th Avenue - 58th Street (West)
710740f-a.text:
11th Avenue, east side, north from W. 58th Sireet. This
thoroughfare loses its identity at 59th Street, to become known as
WTest End Avenue. The cleared lot in the foreground occupies the
entire 58th - 59th Street frontage. Note the vacant site at the
N. E. corner of 59th Street where tbe old Empire Warehouse stood.
October 24, 1939
Views 1,2

710739f-c.title: Manhattan: 11th Avenue - 58th Street (West)
710739f-c.text:
11th Avenue, east side, north from W. 58th Street, showing the
cleared 58th - 59th Street frontage and the beginning of West End
AIenue. The latter, technically starts at 59th Street and therefore
the buildings seen are on same. On the left are the extensive New
York Central Railroad yards.
Views 1,2: May 8, 1935
View 3: November 25, 1937
P. L. Sperr
NO REPRODUICTIONS
